<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-04-0627 </DOCNO><TEXT>In line with the increasing mechanisation of the mining and quarryingindustry, storage bunkers must now be regarded as an essential part ofany transport system and should be capable of manual, remote or automaticoperation. They are integrated into the system and are designed to receivelarge volumes of material at a varying rate, to give storage capacityand to discharge material back into the transport system at the appropriatetime and at the required rate. This article reviews bunkers producedby several companies in UK.</TEXT></DOC>